tobiko/openstack/octavia/_waiters.py.message:
OpenStack code style is pedanting about this. You should only import modules, not final symbols. Example:

 from tobiko.shell import sh

 try:
     sh.execute(...)
 except sh.ShellCommandFailed:

I would keep a list of waited members to avoid requesting more than once to members that are available. Example:

 last_reached_id = 0 # avoid
 for attempt in tobiko.retry(...):
     try:
         for member in members[last_reached_id:]:
             octavia.check_members_balanced()
             last_reached_id += 1. # prevent retrying same member again
     except sh.ShellCommandFailed:
         # It will retry after interval seconds
         LOG.info("Waiting for members to have HTTP service available...")
     else:
         break  # this breaks the attempt loop

